      <h2>Internship/Entry-Level Programs</h2>
      <p>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Google offers various internship and
        entry-level programs for students, including the Google Internship
        Program, Associate Product Manager (APM) Program, and Engineering
        Residency Program. These programs provide hands-on experience and the
        opportunity to work on impactful projects alongside industry
        professionals.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>Education and Skill Requirements</h2>
      <p>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Google typically looks for candidates with
        strong academic backgrounds and a passion for technology and innovation.
        While specific educational requirements vary depending on the role, a
        degree in computer science, engineering, or a related field is often
        preferred. Additionally, Google values skills such as problem-solving,
        critical thinking, coding proficiency, and effective communication.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>Campus Recruitment and Career Fairs</h2>
      <p>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Google actively participates in campus
        recruitment events and career fairs at universities worldwide. They
        often host information sessions and tech talks to connect with students
        and provide insights into their company culture, projects, and
        opportunities.
      </p>
